{
  "text": "Sample size was estimated using Stata Version 9 (StataCorp, College Station, TX) and was based on MCC data from prior studies in adolescent and young adult patients with CF who were treated with HS [CITATION_1] and adult healthy subjects who were treated with placebo [CITATION_2] . In the former study [CITATION_3] , the mean difference in MCC at 1 hour was 4.7% (post HS -baseline values). In the latter study [CITATION_4] , mean MCC \u00b1 standard deviation (SD) at 76 minutes was 12.3 \u00b1 8.3 [CITATION_5] . Since our proposed analysis was a paired comparison of differences within the same child, we assumed a range of values for the SD of the difference in clearance between placebo and HS that was less than the variability of independent measurements observed in these two studies. We determined that a sample size of 12 children would provide 80% power to detect a 5% or larger mean difference in MCC between inhalation of placebo versus HS aerosol, assuming the SD of the paired differences was 6% and assuming a = 0.05 (2-sided). A 5% mean difference between treatments is similar to what was reported by Donaldson et al. [CITATION_6] .",
